result.name: Hee Kee Cart Noodle

reviews.text: First meal in HK, a bit costly but food is ok. Must try the pork intestine
The staff services are average, but it definitely a recommended cart noodles . The photos I posted was how I order my cart noodles .

Located at the intersection of Nanking street in the Jordan area, this place opens early for breakfast though the breakfast items are limited. The food is typical of what you can expect from most Hong Kong restaurants. The price is also good so it's a good place to go to for lunch and dinner if you just want HK standard fare.

Serves decent HK local cart noodle in a cosy, air-conditioned restaurant. One can customise own bowl of noodle by choosing from a variety of noodles, soup base and toppings. Tried the thick beef broth and the taste was yummy !
Select your own ingredients, noodles n soup base. Love their chicken wings stuffed with glutinous rice. Ordered one plate but had to order seconds!!

result.name: Amoy Plaza

reviews.text: Old private estate shopping mall struggling to compete with new ones.  It is not the new huge malls with high ceilings big brands but you may like the surprises and the rare shops at the corners or far end of corridors.  There are a few shops selling expert model kits for adults and toys for teenagers and game console games also.
Many good restaurants, many hobby stores. Something for everyone. Best of all, affordable price.
Many delicious food such as Genki Sushi and Pizza Hut

A lot of choices to choose from, a cinema and stuff like that. What you would hope from a decent shopping mall. There are also housing estates above the shopping centre but ofc it's too expensive for a normal human being in Hong Kong to afford
Nice concentrated shops and diversity.

reviews.text: 招牌四寶麵，包含魚蛋、豬血、牛腩和大腸，材料都軟爛入味，以大骨汁為基底，加上辣油，是一碗好吃的車仔麵。炸雞翅，外酥內嫩，不過就小吃而言，價格有些偏高。
